-->Coroutine vs Thread(SELCS)
Feature				Coroutine											Thread
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Nature				Sequential processing (one is executed at a time)	Concurrent processing (multiple threads at a time)
Execution			Executes in one thread, can suspend and resume		Can be blocked for a period; cannot resume until finished
Lightweight			Lightweight and controlled by the user				Runs independently
Context and Stack	Has its own context and stack						Does not have its own system resources
Synchronization		Asynchronous mechanism								Uses synchronization mechanisms